1.	Who is Erik Reid?
Erik is a potential new board member who is supposed to be a technology hotshot

2.	Why does he take our main character to the production floor?  What is he trying to illustrate?
He wants to show him that managing IT operations is like running a factory. He implies that in order to control the release of work he must learn what the equivalent of the factory’s “release work desk” is in his organization 

3.  List the different kinds of work Erik outlines
a.	Business projects
b.	Internal IT
c.	Changes; if is not supporting our business projects should we be doing them?
